dionul Ion Oblemenco (1967)|A]]||0\u20131||35,000||\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}26 November 1986 || R3 1 ||{{left}}{{flagicon|YUG}} [[Hajduk Split]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||2\u20130||11,569||{{left}}[[Jim McInally|McInally]], [[John Clark (footballer born 1964)|Clark]]\n|- style=\"background:#ffe;\"\n| {{left}}10 December 1986 || R3 2 ||{{left}}{{flagicon|YUG}} [[Hajduk Split]] [[File:TV-icon-2.svg|18px]]||[[Gradski stadion u Poljudu|A]]||0\u20130||26,000||\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}4 March 1987 || QF 1 ||{{left}}{{flagicon|ESP}} [[F.C. Barcelona|Barcelona]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||1\u20130||21,322||{{left}}[[Kevin Gallacher|Gallacher]]\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}18 March 1987 || QF 2 ||{{left}}{{flagicon|ESP}} [[F.C. Barcelona|Barcelona]]||[[Camp Nou|A]]||2\u20131||42,000||{{left}}[[John Clark (footballer born 1964)|Clark]], [[Iain Ferguson|Ferguson]]\n|- style=\"background:#ffe;\"\n| {{left}}8 April 1987 || SF 1 ||{{left}}{{flagicon|DEU}} [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach|M\u00f6nchengladbach]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||0\u20130||15,789||\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}22 April 1987 || SF 2 ||{{left}}{{flagicon|DEU}} [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach|M\u00f6nchengladbach]]||[[B\u00f6kelbergstadion|A]]||2\u20130||33,500||{{left}}[[Iain Ferguson|Ferguson]], [[Ian Redford|Redford]]\n|- style=\"background:#fee;\"\n| {{left}}6 May 1987 || F 1 ||{{left}}{{flagicon|SWE}} [[IFK G\u00f6teborg|Gothenburg]]||[[Ullevi|A]]||0\u20131||50,053||\n|- style=\"background:#ffe;\"\n| {{left}}20 May 1987 || F 2 ||{{left}}{{flagicon|SWE}} [[IFK G\u00f6teborg|Gothenburg]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||1\u20131||20,911||{{left}}[[John Clark (footballer born 1964)|Clark]]\n|}\n\n==Player details==\nDuring the 1986\u201387 season, United used 29 different players comprising four nationalities. [[Billy Thomson]] was the only player to feature in every match of United's [[UEFA Cup]] run. The table below shows the number of appearances and goals scored by each player.<ref name=\"stats\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dirtyarab.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/History/1986s/1986-87/86-87page.htm|title=1986\u201387|work=Glenrothes Arabs|accessdate=8 February 2008}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>\n{{Extended football squad start|[[Scottish Premier Division]]|Tennent's [[Scottish Cup]]|[[Scottish League Cup|Skol Cup]]|[[UEFA Cup]]}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Alan Main]]|pos=GK|nat=Scotland|2|0|1|0|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Billy Thomson]]|pos=GK|nat=Scotland|39|0|6|0|4|0|12|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Scott Y. Thomson]]|pos=GK|nat=Scotland|3|0|0|0|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Dave Beaumont]]|pos=DF|nat=Scotland|28|0|4|0|2|0|6|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[John Clark (footballer born 1964)|John Clark]]|pos=DF|nat=Scotland|30|3|6|0|1|0|10|4}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Richard Gough]]|pos=DF|nat=Scotland|3|1|0|0|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Paul Hegarty]]|pos=DF|nat=Scotland|23|4|4|1|4|0|7|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[John Holt (footballer, born 1956)|John Holt]]|pos=DF|nat=Scotland|18|0|4|1|2|0|7|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Maurice Malpas]]|pos=DF|nat=Scotland|36|0|7|1|4|0|10|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Gary McGinnis]]|pos=DF|nat=Scotland|20|0|0|0|1|0|4|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Dave Narey]]|pos=DF|nat=Scotland|33|0|7|0|4|0|10|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Chris Sulley]]|pos=DF|nat=England|7|0|0|0|0|0|1|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Brian Welsh]]|pos=DF|nat=Scotland|1|0|0|0|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Eamonn Bannon]]|pos=MF|nat=Scotland|38|9|4|0|4|0|11|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[David Bowman (footballer born 1964)|Dave Bowman]]|pos=MF|nat=Scotland|29|0|2|0|1|0|6|0}}\n{{Extended football squad p