 players were sold by the club during the season with a public total of nearly \u00a31,000,000. One player retired due to injury.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%\"\n|-\n! Date !! Player !! To !! Fee\n|-\n| 1 August 1986 || {{flagicon|SCO}} {{sortname|Richard|Gough}} || [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] || \u00a30,750,000<ref name=\"gough\">{{cite web|url=http://www.arabarchive.co.uk/player.php?id=32|title=Richard Gough|publisher=The Arab Archive|accessdate=14 April 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 13 December 1986 || {{flagicon|SCO|IRE}} {{sortname|Tommy|Coyne}} || [[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]] || \u00a30,075,000<ref name=\"coyne\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dirtyarab.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/Player%20a-z/Coyne%20T.htm|title=Player A to Z: Tommy Coyne|publisher=Glenrothes Arabs|accessdate=8 February 2008|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081015114417/http://www.dirtyarab.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/Player%20a-z/Coyne%20T.htm |archivedate = 15 October 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{0}}{{0}} January 1987 || {{flagicon|SCO}} {{sortname|Ralph|Milne}} || [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]] || \u00a30,125,000<ref name=\"milne\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dirtyarab.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/Player%20a-z/Milne%20R.htm|title=Player A to Z: Ralph Milne|publisher=Glenrothes Arabs|accessdate=8 February 2008|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081015120834/http://www.dirtyarab.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/Player%20a-z/Milne%20R.htm |archivedate = 15 October 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| || {{flagicon|ENG}} {{sortname|Chris|Sulley}} || [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]] || \u00a30,015,000<ref name=\"sulleyout\">{{cite web|url=http://www.arabarchive.co.uk/player.php?id=200|title=Chris Sulley|date=14 April 2015|publisher=The Arab Archive}}</ref>\n|-\n| || {{flagicon|SCO}} {{sortname|Jimmy|Page|Jimmy Page (footballer)}} || Retired || N/A\n|}\n\n====Loans out====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%\"\n|-\n! Date !! Player !! To !! Duration\n|-\n| || {{flagicon|ENG}} {{sortname|Chris|Sulley}} || [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]] || Unknown<ref name=\"sulleyout\"/>\n|}\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Playing kit==\n{| style=\"border:0;\"\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{Football kit\n| pattern_la = _blackline\n| pattern_b  = _vneckblack\n| pattern_ra = _blackline\n| leftarm    = EE7700\n| body       = EE7700\n| rightarm   = EE7700\n| shorts     = 000000\n| socks      = EE7700\n| title      = Home<br />colours\n}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{Football kit\n| pattern_la = _blackline\n| pattern_b  = _vneckblack\n| pattern_ra = _blackline\n| leftarm    = FFFFFF\n| body       = FFFFFF\n| rightarm   = FFFFFF\n| shorts     = 000000\n| socks      = FFFFFF\n| title      = Away<br />colours\n}}\n|}\nThe shirts were sponsored by future chairman [[Eddie Thompson]]'s VG Foodstores for a second season.\n\n==See also==\n*[[1986\u201387 in Scottish football]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.bbc.co.uk/scotland/sportscotland/asportingnation/article/0048/ BBC's 'A Sporting Nation' review of the UEFA Cup run]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080703194539/http://www.dirtyarab.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/History/1980s/1986-87/86-87page.htm Glenrothes Arabs 1986\u201387 season review]\n\n{{Dundee United F.C.}}\n{{Dundee United F.C. seasons}}\n{{1986-87 in Scottish football}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dundee United F.C. Season 1986-87}}\n[[Category:Dundee United F.C. seasons|1986-87]]\n[[Category:Scottish football clubs 1986\u201387 season]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use British English|date=March 2012}}\n{{Infobox Football club season\n| club = [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]\n| logo = [[File:Dufc.gif]]\n| season = 1986\u201387\n| manager = [[Jim McLean]]\n| chairman = George Fox\n| league = [[Scottish Football League Premier Division|Scottish Premier Division]]\n| league result = 3rd ([[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]])<br />W24 D12 L8 F66 A36 P60\n| cup1 = [[Tennent's]] [[Scottish Cup]]| cup1 result = Runners-up\n| cup2 = [[Scottish League Cup|Skol Cup]] | cup2 result = Semi-finals\n| cup3 = [[UEFA Cup]] | cup3 result = Runners-up\n| league topscorer = [[Iain Ferguson]] (16)\n| season topscorer = [[Iain Ferguson]] (28)\n| highest attendance =\n| lowest attendance =\n| prevseason = [[1985\u201386 Dundee United F.C. season|1985\u201386]]\n| nextseason = [[1987\u201388 Dundee United F.C. season|1987\u201388]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1986\u201387 season''' was the 78th year of [[association football|football]] played by [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]], and covers the period from 1 July 1986 to 30 June 1987. United finished in third place, securing [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]] football for the following season.  They reached the [[Scottish Cup]] final, only to lose after extra-time to [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]].  The season is most notable for the club's run to the UEFA Cup Final, knocking out [[F.C. Barcelona|Barcelona]], [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]] and [[CS Universitatea Craiova|Universitatea Craiova]] en route.  United lost 2-1 on aggregate to [[IFK Gothenburg]] in the final.\n\n==Match results==\nDundee United played a total of 67 competitive matches during the 1986\u201387 season.<ref name=\"results\">{{cite web|url=http://www.arabarchive.co.uk/matches.php?|title=Match results 1986/1987|work=Arab Archive|accessdate=14 November 2016}}</ref> The team finished third in the [[Scottish Premier Division]].\n\nIn the cup competitions, United lost in the final of the [[Scottish Cup]] to [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]] and lost in the [[Scottish League Cup|Skol Cup]] semi-finals. [[Sweden|Swedish]] side [[IFK Goteborg|Gothenburg]] defeated United in the final of the [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]] over two legs.\n\n===Legend===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#efe;\"|<small>Win</small>\n| style=\"background:#ffe;\"|<small>Draw</small>\n| style=\"background:#fee;\"|<small>Loss</small>\n|}\n\nAll results are written with Dundee United's score first.\n\n===Premier Division===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Date!!Opponent!!Venue!!Result!!Attendance!!Scorers\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}9 August 1986 ||{{left}}[[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||2\u20131||10,910||{{left}}[[Richard Gough|Gough]], [[Ian Redford|Redford]]\n|- style=\"background:#ffe;\"\n| {{left}}13 August 1986 ||{{left}}[[Clydebank F.C.|Clydebank]]||[[Kilbowie Park|A]]||0\u20130||1,612||\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}16 August 1986 ||{{left}}[[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]||[[Ibrox Stadium|A]]||3\u20132||43,995||{{left}}[[Kevin Gallacher|Gallacher]], [[Ian Redford|Redford]]\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}23 August 1986 ||{{left}}[[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Hearts]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||1\u20130||11,068||{{left}}[[Paul Hegarty|Hegarty]]\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}30 August 1986 ||{{left}}[[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||3\u20130||6,168||{{left}}[[Iain Ferguson|Ferguson]], [[Kevin Gallacher|Gallacher]], [[Eamonn Bannon|Bannon]]\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}6 September 1986 ||{{left}}[[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]||[[Dens Park|A]]||2\u20130||12,079||{{left}}[[Ralph Milne|Milne]], [[Eamonn Bannon|Bannon]]\n|- style=\"background:#ffe;\"\n| {{left}}13 September 1986 ||{{left}}[[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||2\u20132||19,792||{{left}}[[Iain Ferguson|Ferguson]], [[Kevin Gallacher|Gallacher]]\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}20 September 1986 ||{{left}}[[Hamilton Academical F.C.|Hamilton Academical]]||[[Douglas Park|A]]||5\u20131||2,876||{{left}}[[Paul Hegarty|Hegarty]] (2), [[Iain Ferguson|Ferguson]] (2), [[Paul Sturrock|Sturrock]]\n|- style=\"background:#ffe;\"\n| {{left}}27 September 1986 ||{{left}}[[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]]||[[Easter Road|A]]||1\u20131||5,407||{{left}}[[Ian Redford|Redford]]\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}4 October 1986 ||{{left}}[[Falkirk F.C.|Falkirk]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||2\u20130||5,957||{{left}}[[Iain Ferguson|Ferguson]] (2)\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}8 October 1986 ||{{left}}[[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||4\u20130||5,740||{{left}}''[[John Philliben|Philliben]]'', [[Iain Ferguson|Ferguson]], ''[[Fraser Wishart|Wishart]]'', [[Tommy Coyne|Coyne]]\n|- style=\"background:#fee;\"\n| {{left}}11 October 1986 ||{{left}}[[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]||[[Pittodrie Stadium|A]]||0\u20132||14,922||\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}18 October 1986 ||{{left}}[[Clydebank F.C.|Clydebank]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||2\u20130||5,314||{{left}}''[[Stuart Auld|Auld]]'', [[Eamonn Bannon|Bannon]]\n|- style=\"background:#ffe;\"\n| {{left}}25 October 1986 ||{{left}}[[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Hearts]]||[[Tynecastle Park|A]]||2\u20132||14,320||{{left}}[[Paul Sturrock|Sturrock]] (2)\n|- style=\"background:#ffe;\"\n| {{left}}29 October 1986 ||{{left}}[[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||0\u20130||20,171||\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}1 November 1986 ||{{left}}[[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]]||[[Love Street|A]]||1\u20130||3,930||{{left}}[[Iain Ferguson|Ferguson]]\n|- style=\"background:#fee;\"\n| {{left}}8 November 1986 ||{{left}}[[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||0\u20133||11,733||\n|- style=\"background:#fee;\"\n| {{left}}15 November 1986 ||{{left}}[[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]||[[Celtic Park|A]]||0\u20131||34,319||\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}19 November 1986 ||{{left}}[[Hamilton Academical F.C.|Hamilton Academical]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||3\u20130||4,280||{{left}}[[John Clark (footballer born 1964)|Clark]], [[Iain Ferguson|Ferguson]], [[Paul Sturrock|Sturrock]]\n|- style=\"background:#efe;\"\n| {{left}}22 November 1986 ||{{left}}[[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||1\u20130||6,862||{{left}}[[Eamonn Bannon|Bannon]]\n|- style=\"background:#fee;\"\n| {{left}}29 November 1986 ||{{left}}[[Falkirk F.C.|Falkirk]]||[[Brockville Park|A]]||1\u20132||4,500||{{lef